text: Alexandrovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Alexandrovsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 520 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 25 km from Meleuz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Meleuzovsky District
title: Alexandrovka, Meleuzovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
